>First person
You can tell the whole story from two perspectives. You want the reader to really get connected with the protags. You need the internal thoughts of a character often.

>Third person
Story needs to be told by multiple people. The reader needs a greater perspective. You're confident you can connect the reader to the protagonists without internal thoughts. You're comfortable with using dialogue often.

>Second person
You haven't learned how to not write a green yet. You're writing a self-insert anon. Please, don't use second person.
